<blockquote>
<p>&quot;Testing of SCP-906 which involved placing a Class D and a cow into a testing chamber with SCP-906 resulted in SCP-906 targeting the Class D before the cow.&quot; (run on sentence)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Er, no, it's not. Awkward and unwieldy, maybe (I do think it might benefit from revision), but not a run-on and not inherently incorrect. The phrase &quot;which involved placing a Class D and a cow into a testing chamber with SCP-906&quot; is an adjectival phrase modifying &quot;Testing.&quot; It can't stand on it's own, and if you take it out, you get &quot;Testing of SCP-906 resulted in SCP-906 targeting the Class D before the cow,&quot; which is a perfectly valid sentence.</p>

